<subSubSection pageId="426" pageNumber="427" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="82632394-ED63-5F41-914F-63B97D36646D" authority="Netolitzky, 1911" authorityName="Netolitzky" authorityYear="1911" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Eupetedromus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="426" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eupetedromus">Eupetedromus Netolitzky, 1911</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="426" pageNumber="427" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Netolitzky" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eupetedromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="426" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eupetedromus</taxonomicName>
Netolitzky, 1911: 190. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1787" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="426" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">Carabus dentellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thunberg, 1787 designated by Jeannel (1941b: 451). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">eupetes</emphasis>
(easy) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">dromos</emphasis>
(running) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="426" pageNumber="427" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">
Eleven species in the Nearctic (five species) and Palaearctic (seven species) Regions. One species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1860" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="426" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incrematum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">Bembidion incrematum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is Holarctic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="426" pageNumber="427" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="426" pageNumber="427">
Bousquet and Webster (2006) provided a key for the identification of all North American species. Lindroth (1963b: 348-351, 360) covered four species, three he placed in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">incrematum</emphasis>
group, the other (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="426" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">Bembidion variegatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="426" pageNumber="427">dorsale</emphasis>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
